{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MjrCPqnuDcHxGqwUCW1AwG","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t<!-- This file is managed by the ai-builder pipeline. Do not hand-edit. -->\n2\t# Task: doc-1\n3\t\n4\t## Goal\n5\tGenerate documentation for the platform-monolith source tree. Produce companion\n6\t`.md` files for every source file, a `README.md` in every directory, and\n7\tcross-component synthesis docs (`data-flow.md`, `api.md`) at composite levels.\n8\t\n9\tThe source tree is a Go HTTP service with two internal service packages:\n10\t\n11\t```\n12\tcmd/platform/\n13\t  main.go                            ← service entry point (wires metrics + iam)\n14\tinternal/\n15\t  metrics/\n16\t    metrics.go                       ← package wiring: store + handlers\n17\t    store/\n18\t      store.go                       ← in-memory event store\n19\t    handlers/\n20\t      handlers.go                    ← HTTP handlers for POST/GET /events\n21\t  iam/\n22\t    iam.go                           ← package wiring: lifecycle + authz\n23\t    lifecycle/\n24\t      lifecycle.go                   ← user CRUD + token auth\n25\t    authz/\n26\t      authz.go                       ← RBAC roles and permission checks\n27\t```\n28\t\n29\tSome directories already have a `README.md` (`internal/iam/` and\n30\t`internal/metrics/`). The pipeline must co-exist with these pre-existing docs —\n31\tit should add companion `.md` files and sub-directory `README.md` files where\n32\tthey are missing, and produce synthesis docs at composite levels.\n33\t\n34\t## Context\n35\tThis is a regression test for the ai-builder doc pipeline.\n36\t\n37\tThe pipeline must:\n38\t- Traverse the source tree recursively\n39\t- At each leaf directory (atomic): read source files, write companion `.md` files\n40\t  and a `README.md` describing the package\n41\t- At each composite directory (after all leaves complete): write cross-component\n42\t  synthesis docs (`data-flow.md`, `api.md`, `README.md`) using the completed\n43\t  sub-component handoff summaries\n44\t- Never modify source files — only create `.md` files\n45\t- Co-exist gracefully with pre-existing `.md` files in the source tree\n46\t\n47\tThe output directory IS the source tree. All generated `.md` files are written\n48\tinline alongside the source files they document.\n49\t\n50\t## Components\n51\t\n52\t_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n53\t\n54\t## Design\n55\t\n56\t_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n57\t\n58\t## Acceptance Criteria\n59\t\n60\t_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n61\t\n62\t## Test Command\n63\t\n64\t_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n65\t\n66\t## Suggested Tools\n67\t\n68\t_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n69\t\n70\t## Notes\n71\t\n72\t_None._\n73\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7eb11384-7a46-4372-bc87-f72009b07f09","uuid":"dffdd274-1622-412a-bb58-49a8fefe5a11","timestamp":"2026-04-05T22:24:04.798Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/establish-regression-recordings/sandbox/regressions/doc-platform-monolith/target/project/tasks/main/in-progress/f8673c-doc-platform-monolith/f8673c-0000-doc-1/README.md","content":"<!-- This file is managed by the ai-builder pipeline. Do not hand-edit. -->\n# Task: doc-1\n\n## Goal\nGenerate documentation for the platform-monolith source tree. Produce companion\n`.md` files for every source file, a `README.md` in every directory, and\ncross-component synthesis docs (`data-flow.md`, `api.md`) at composite levels.\n\nThe source tree is a Go HTTP service with two internal service packages:\n\n```\ncmd/platform/\n  main.go                            ← service entry point (wires metrics + iam)\ninternal/\n  metrics/\n    metrics.go                       ← package wiring: store + handlers\n    store/\n      store.go                       ← in-memory event store\n    handlers/\n      handlers.go                    ← HTTP handlers for POST/GET /events\n  iam/\n    iam.go                           ← package wiring: lifecycle + authz\n    lifecycle/\n      lifecycle.go                   ← user CRUD + token auth\n    authz/\n      authz.go                       ← RBAC roles and permission checks\n```\n\nSome directories already have a `README.md` (`internal/iam/` and\n`internal/metrics/`). The pipeline must co-exist with these pre-existing docs —\nit should add companion `.md` files and sub-directory `README.md` files where\nthey are missing, and produce synthesis docs at composite levels.\n\n## Context\nThis is a regression test for the ai-builder doc pipeline.\n\nThe pipeline must:\n- Traverse the source tree recursively\n- At each leaf directory (atomic): read source files, write companion `.md` files\n  and a `README.md` describing the package\n- At each composite directory (after all leaves complete): write cross-component\n  synthesis docs (`data-flow.md`, `api.md`, `README.md`) using the completed\n  sub-component handoff summaries\n- Never modify source files — only create `.md` files\n- Co-exist gracefully with pre-existing `.md` files in the source tree\n\nThe output directory IS the source tree. All generated `.md` files are written\ninline alongside the source files they document.\n\n## Components\n\n_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n\n## Design\n\n_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n\n## Test Command\n\n_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n\n## Suggested Tools\n\n_To be completed by the ARCHITECT._\n\n## Notes\n\n_None._\n","numLines":73,"startLine":1,"totalLines":73}}}
