{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01D41vrjrdfs1CpWqXJDBHF4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. The `lifecycle/` directory contains:\n- `lifecycle.go` — the source file to document\n- `lifecycle_test.go` — skip per policy\n- `README.md` — a placeholder stub, needs to be replaced\n\nI need to:\n1. Create `lifecycle.go.md` (missing)\n2. Update `README.md` from placeholder stub\n\nLet me analyze `lifecycle.go`:\n\n**Types:**\n- `User` — domain model with ID, Username, PasswordHash\n- `Token` — active session token with Token (string) and UserID\n\n\n- `Store` — in-memory state with RWMutex, users map (id→User), byName map (username→id), tokens map (token→Token)\n- `Handler` — exposes lifecycle HTTP endpoints\n- `errDuplicate` — typed error string for duplicate username\n\n**Public API:**\n- `New() *Handler` — constructs a Handler with fresh in-memory Store\n- `(h *Handler) RegisterRoutes(mux *http.ServeMux)` — registers lifecycle endpoints onto mux\n\n**Routes registered:**\n- `POST /users` — create user (bcrypt password, returns id+username)\n- `GET /users/{id}` — fetch user by ID\n- `DELETE /users/{id}` — remove user (appears to be cut off but likely deletes by ID)\n- `POST /auth/login` — authenticate and issue token\n- `POST /auth/logout` — revoke token with Bearer auth\n\nThe implementation uses RWMutex for thread-safe access, with separate helper methods handling user CRUD and token lifecycle. Password hashing relies on bcrypt, and I'm pulling in UUID generation and crypto libraries as external dependencies.\n\nNow I'm writing the documentation files to explain the API and setup.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2735,"cache_read_input_tokens":20214,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2735},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":